    </encoding>
    <source>Music source: The Methodist Hymnal, 1905.  Hymn 310.</source>
    <miscellaneous>
      <miscellaneous-field name="lyrics">6.No condemnation now I dread; Jesus, and all in Him, is mine;
Alive in Him, my living Head, And clothed in righteousness divine,
Bold I approach th'eternal throne, And claim the crown, through Christ my own.</miscellaneous-field>
    </miscellaneous>
  </identification>
